Recently released SAPS crime statistics show an increase in crime, particularly residential robberies and hijackings. Key is vigilance, an understanding of how and when such crimes are most likely to happen, and taking active measures to mitigate them; especially during the festive season when we typically see an uptick in criminal activities, says Mandy Barrett of insurance brokerage and risk advisors, Aon South Africa.There is a great deal that can be done to mitigate your risk. Aon provides the following 10 tips and insights that can possibly reduce your risk:READ MORE: Crime stats for MpumalangaREAD MORE: Drones to help assist in the fight against crime